She turned to a blank page and wrote the date on it. Then, she wrote below the date: "5/11/648-12/13/648."
"Aren't you looking back on the past?" Avery asked, looking at the old notebook. Carly nodded. "Do you think they'll let you go home for Christmas? There are only a few days left until Christmas."
Carly tapped the lantern twice, indicating "no." Not surprising to Avery. The Ice King never allowed Carly to go outside, because in his eyes, Carly was "a flaw." Carly was born mute and was the only girl in her family; all the other children were boys.
Avery is also like that, in their unique way. When Avery came out as non-binary, the world seemed to change as well. As a punishment for their uniqueness, Avery was often left to work alone for most of the time.
TA was also forced to be the princess's servant. However, TA didn't mind, because TA had a friend.
"Aren't your birthday coming up soon?" Avery asked, remembering that Princess's birthday was just a few days away. Carly nodded, a hint of sadness flickering in her light blue eyes.
"Want to celebrate a bit?" TA asked, recalling how Carly had answered the question the last time.
No. Carly tapped the table. Avery knew this was a hard topic for Carly to bring up. That very day, she had been locked in this room while her mother was executed. When it happened, Avery was still an infant, but they remembered the anger of the servants and citizens at that time. Avery had heard that Queen Elwin was a good queen and even had the ability to predict future events.
"So... what do you want to do?" asked TA. Carly looked up at TA, her eyes shining with excitement. She handed Avery a piece of paper. However, when he looked down...
6-inch X 6-inch canvas
White, blue pigments of varying shades
6 brushes of different sizes
Easel
"Are you trying to get me to bring these things for you?" Avery turned to the silent princess, who was continuously tapping away, her ponytail swaying back and forth. "Is that right?" When he saw the usually quiet and reserved princess so enthusiastic about something, he couldn't help but giggle. This was the first time she wanted something outside her room, and it had nothing to do with books.
"Okay! See you later!" Avery said, standing up and stepping through the scattered papers and notebooks.
Carly nodded, continued to burrow deeper into the thick blankets, and reflected on her memories.
TA stepped out of the room, thinking that the princess was finally willing to try new things and had made some requests beyond her capability (such as paint), which made TA feel relieved.
TA once again crossed through the hall, making an effort not to listen to the servants' hushed whispers.
"I heard that she was possessed by Queen Elwin, so she always goes to that room."
"I heard that she was eating children in that room."
"Is it normal for her to look like a man?"
TA could no longer bear to hear these words, so had to cover his ears. He went to the room of the royal painter, which was in the east wing, the second door on the left.
Avery arrived at the door, just as ornate as Carly's. Painted on the door was a white dragon, one of the six primordial dragons, said to have created the Frostland realm. It's no wonder the painter favored history, as it was natural to depict the white dragon on the door.
TA opened the door, expecting everything to be as before. For example, there were paints everywhere, pencils and papers scattered on the floor, and the easels covering every inch of the walls. However, the scene inside the room was entirely different. The room was clean, with a red velvet backdrop and a chair. Sitting on the chair was Prince Aquiro, painting a portrait.
"Oh, good morning, Avery! Want to see the portrait of your future king?" Aquilero asked, winking at Avery.
"Sorry, Your Highness," TA replied, starting to search around for what Princess Carly wanted. "I was just coming to get some art supplies."
"Little one, are you leaving so soon?" Aguero asked, "But I still want to see you!"
"I don't want to," Avery found the art supplies on the list and put them into a box. "And I'm not a girl either."
The prince shook his head. "Oh, my dear, you know this is just a phase! It'll pass when you grow up!" he said vaguely.
"I have to go," said TA, suddenly feeling very uncomfortable, because the prince was still prattling on. TA recalled all the negative comments people had made about TA's gender identity. I really want to get rid of him.
"Are you leaving so quickly?" The prince appeared at the door instantly, ignoring the royal painter's call.
"This is not the behavior of a future king!" TA shouted fiercely.
"No one will ever know. People won't believe you, and if that painter still valued his own life, he wouldn't have said such things carelessly," the prince said, turning his head to look at the painter, then leaning in close to Avery. "What do you think about going out on a date?" Avery trembled with fear. Of course, Avery had heard a lot of threats before, but none had come from the prince, let alone from the future king.
"Do you know what the character 'bù' means?" he roared, shoving the prince aside with one hand.
"No," Aguero smiled and answered. The crown prince, who could have anything he wanted, naturally had no idea what the word "no" meant.
Avery rolled her eyes. "Why so many people, and you just happen to want to go out with me? How many admirers do you have? A hundred?"
He laughed and interrupted, "To be precise, over five hundred." He shook his hair, swaying in the cold wind.
"Look! Why me? I'm the curse of the palace." He hugged his arms.
"Aquiro placed a finger on Avery's chin, forcing her to look up at him."
